get=\"#feedbackModal_main_2529998\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Okt 13, 2022</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent wide\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104mnm1665702976003.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/mnm1665702976003.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/mnm1665702976003.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"mnm1665702976003\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      DBMS Connectors on a Network\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Uniface supports multiple DBMS connectors and multiple network connections. Uniface applications can connect to the DBMS connector directly or remotely.\n </p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"mnm1665702976003__p_d61904e1_d61905e1_d61906e1\">Normally, remote database access is handled by a Uniface Router and Uniface Server on a remote machine that is accessible via a Uniface network connector. In this case, the DBMS connector is located on the same machine as the Uniface Server.</p>\n<figure class=\"fig fignone\" id=\"mnm1665702976003__fig_d61907e1_d61908e1_d61909e1\"><figcaption><span class=\"fig--title-label\">Figure 1. </span>Connectors in a Uniface Application and Application Server Configuration</figcaption>\n<img alt=\"Diagram showing Connectors in a Uniface Application and Application Server Configuration\" class=\"image\" src=\"https://docs-be.rocketsoftware.com/bundle/uniface_104/page/connectors1.jpg?_LANG=enus\"/>\n</figure>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"mnm1665702976003__p_d61913e1_d61914e1_d61915e1\">However, it is also possible to use a network product provided by the DBMS. In this case, the DBMS connector and the Uniface application reside on the same machine.</p>\n<figure class=\"fig fignone\" id=\"mnm1665702976003__fig_d61916e1_d61917e1_d61918e1\"><figcaption><span class=\"fig--title-label\">Figure 2. </span>Example of Uniface Interaction with the Networking Facility of the DBMS</figcaption>\n<img alt=\"Diagram showing Uniface Interaction with the Networking Facility of the DBMS\" class=\"image\" src=\"https://docs-be.rocketsoftware.com/bundle/uniface_104/page/connectors3.jpg?_LANG=enus\"/>\n</figure>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2529998\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2529998\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "DBMS Connectors on a Network Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Okt 13, 2022 Summarize Uniface 10.4 DBMS Connectors on a Network Uniface supports multiple DBMS connectors and multiple network connections. Uniface applications can connect to the DBMS connector directly or remotely. Normally, remote database access is handled by a Uniface Router and Uniface Server on a remote machine that is accessible via a Uniface network connector. In this case, the DBMS connector is located on the same machine as the Uniface Server. Figure 1. Connectors in a Uniface Application and Application Server Configuration However, it is also possible to use a network product provided by the DBMS. In this case, the DBMS connector and the Uniface application reside on the same machine. Figure 2. Example of Uniface Interaction with the Networking Facility of the DBMS Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}